title._content: Portrait of a woman, possibly Ethel Manila Sterling, c 1913

description._content: This photograph depicts a woman seated wearing a lace embroidered dress. It is possible that she is American shipowner, Captain Edward Robert Sterling's, first daughter Ethel Manila Sterling. Ethel Manila Sterling was born on 20 February 1895 (or 1897) in Manila, the Philippines. She married Harry T Kelsh Junior and, according to the 1920 US census, she was 23 and he was 30 years old at the time. Listed as a housewife, this information was crossed out and replaced with the word ‘none’. Her husband Harry was born in Pennsylvania and served as a commissioned officer in the US Coast and Geodetic Survey from April 1911 to September 1917, and as 1st lieutenant in the Air Service from that time until December 1918. By 1930 US Census, he was working in finance in the banking industry. For more information see our blog post on the Sterlings: bit.ly/OsqaFc This photo is part of the Australian National Maritime Museum’s Samuel J. Hood Studio collection. Sam Hood (1872-1953) was a Sydney photographer with a passion for ships. His 60-year career spanned the romantic age of sail and two world wars. The photos in the collection were taken mainly in Sydney and Newcastle during the first half of the 20th century. The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. This record has been updated accordingly. Photographer: Samuel J. Hood Studio Collection Object no. 00023163
